UNWIND [{_id:1213, properties:{quote:"what do you think?"}}, {_id:1216, properties:{quote:"yes - tammie still trying to find a room"}}, {_id:1219, properties:{quote:"can you let frank and laura's group know"}}, {_id:1224, properties:{quote:"to: kitchen, louise"}}, {_id:1229, properties:{quote:"we are therefore holding a  short meeting at 9:00am tomorrow morning"}}, {_id:1232, properties:{quote:"tammie to advise on the room"}}, {_id:1233, properties:{quote:"the below meeting will be held in 30c1"}}, {_id:1236, properties:{quote:"please invite all of your groups"}}, {_id:1302, properties:{quote:"at ferc"}}, {_id:1306, properties:{quote:"on ComEd's side"}}, {_id:1308, properties:{quote:"we plan to file the Enron response"}}, {_id:1311, properties:{quote:"Dynegy wants ComEd to only allow"}}, {_id:1313, properties:{quote:"on ComEd's network transmission system"}}, {_id:1317, properties:{quote:"susan and i will circulate a draft response against dynegy's position later today."}}, {_id:1319, properties:{quote:"ComEd plans to file a lengthy answer disputing dynegy"}}, {_id:1321, properties:{quote:"enron will respond similarly"}}, {_id:1324, properties:{quote:"dynegy stating that there are no transmission problems"}}, {_id:1328, properties:{quote:"as i mentioned in my previous e-mail, on october 17 dynegy filed a complaint against comed."}}, {_id:1331, properties:{quote:"dynegy challenges comed's published business practice that allows 'marketer firm' (firm ld) contracts to be designated as network resources."}}, {_id:1334, properties:{quote:"dynegy argues that this practice conflicts with the oatt provisions that 1) network resources are generation 'owned, purchased or leased by the network customer designated to serve network load,' and 2) a network customer 'must demonstrate that it owns or has committed to purchase generation pursuant to an executed contract' in order to designate a network resource."}}] AS row
